    <item>
      <title>市场综述：亚洲股市有望上涨，因美国大选备受关注</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-28/stock-market-today-dow-s-p-live-updates</link>
      <description><![CDATA[由于交易员们为美国大选和将为美联储下次决策奠定基础的关键经济数据做准备，大多数亚洲股市将跟随华尔街走高。由于交易员们评估政治前景，日本股市可能会停滞不前。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-28/stock-market-today-dow-s-p-live-updates</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2024 22:29:38 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>日元仍是美国大选避风港</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-28/embattled-yen-emerges-victorious-as-ultimate-us-election-haven</link>
      <description><![CDATA[尽管今年日元一直处于疲软状态，但历史表明，对于躲避美国总统大选影响的投资者来说，日元仍然有望成为意外的避风港。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-28/embattled-yen-emerges-victorious-as-ultimate-us-election-haven</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2024 22:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
